      <processinfo id="aspace_af7dc3be10a3d504306c9da9d48a9359">
         <head>Processing Information</head>
         <p>Yale University records are arranged and described at the accession level by the creating office. The University Archives creates collection level descriptive records, but typically does no further arrangement and description at the accession level.</p>  
      </processinfo>
      <scopecontent id="aspace_b8df1708d48edcfbcbebf9c0165b319d">
         <head>Scope and Contents</head>
         <p>The records consist of articles of association, constitution, amendments, and minutes of meetings documenting the activities and operations of the Yale Club of Washington, D.C.</p>  
      </scopecontent>
      <arrangement id="aspace_2a5f24346ba0938ec374294e01faab4c">
         <head>Arrangement</head>
         <p>The records are arranged by accession.</p>  
